            "# Competitors Differenciation\n\nPerson: Astroboy \nTags: Partners\n\n## Berally\n\nCore Platform: Social media network for Berachain ecosystem\n\nKey Features:\n\n- Asset-backed social tokens for creators\n- Marketplace for social token trading\n- Content creation and distribution system\n- Points-based reward system for engagement\n- Integrated wallet for token management\n\nTarget Users:\n\n- Content creators\n- Community members\n- Token traders\n\nRevenue Model:\n\n- Trading fees from social tokens\n- Premium features\n- Creator tools\n\nCurrent Stage:\n\n- Development phase\n- Community building\n- Initial feature testing\n\n## HoneyChat\n\nCore Platform: SocialFi chat application with financial features\n\nKey Features:\n\n- Social derivative trading (friend shorting)\n- Reputation badge system\n- BeraDrops integration\n- Community chat rooms\n- Social token mechanics\n\nTarget Users:\n\n- Active traders\n- Community managers\n- Social investors\n\nRevenue Model:\n\n- Trading fees\n- Premium features\n- Badge system monetization\n\nCurrent Stage:\n\n- Alpha testing\n- Badge system implementation\n- Community growth phase\n\n## Tierra\n\nCore Platform: Influence verification and community management platform\n\nKey Differentiators:\n\n1. Real-World Verification\n- PoM system verifies actual networking\n- Physical interaction validation\n- No other platform offers this\n1. Structured Community System\n- Planet NFTs with clear utility\n- Tiered access through Rockets\n- More sophisticated than basic groups/chats\n1. Achievement System\n- Verifiable milestones\n- Customizable quests\n- Corporate/event integration capability\n1. Professional Focus\n- B2B integration possibilities\n- Event-centric features\n- Enterprise solutions\n\nMarket Position:\n\n- Berally focuses on content/social tokens\n- HoneyChat emphasizes trading/chat\n- Tierra uniquely bridges real and digital networking\n\nTarget Market Differentiation:\n\n- Berally: Content creators and consumers\n- HoneyChat: Traders and chat communities\n- Tierra: Professional networkers, event attendees, community builders\n\n## Competitive Advantages Matrix\n\n| Feature | Berally | HoneyChat | Tierra 2.0 |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Real-world verification | No | No | Yes (PoM) |\n| Community structure | Basic groups | Chat rooms | Planet NFTs |\n| Token system | Social tokens | Social derivatives | Access keys |\n| Revenue streams | Trading fees | Trading & badges | Multi-tier model |\n| Target audience | Content focus | Trading focus | Network focus |\n| Enterprise features | Limited | No | Yes |\n| Event integration | No | No | Yes |\n| Achievement system | Basic points | Badges | Custom quests |\n\n## Market Opportunity\n\nTierra 2.0's focus on real-world verification and professional networking fills a crucial gap:\n\n- Other platforms focus on digital-only interactions\n- No competitor addresses real-world networking verification\n- Growing demand for verified professional connections in Web3",
            "# Tierra Concept Short Memo\n\nPerson: Astroboy \nTags: Product\n\n## Tokenize Your Influence, Amplify Your Impact\n\n**Tierra: Where Influence Meets Value**\n\n### Vision\n\nTierra is revolutionizing how real-world influence is quantified, verified, and monetized in the digital age.\n\n### Core Innovation\n\n**Influence Tokenization System**\nOur primary innovation creates a verifiable measure of social influence through:\n\n- Proof of Meeting (PoM): Validates real-world networking and connections through a personal verification system\n- Achievement Badges: Recognizes participation, accomplishments, and community engagement through customizable quests and milestones\n- Combined, these elements create a unique \"Influence Score\" that truly represents a user's social capital and real-world impact\n\n**Community Spaces**\nSupporting our core influence system, we've developed an innovative community management solution:\n\n- Planet NFTs: Unique digital spaces for creators to build and cultivate their communities\n- Rockets System: Tiered access mechanism that unlocks enhanced features as communities grow\n- Gamified Engagement: Interactive elements that encourage consistent participation and growth\n\n### Market Solution\n\nTierra addresses key challenges in both Web3 and traditional networking:\n\n- Verification of real-world influence and connections\n- Monetization of authentic community engagement\n- Bridging online and offline social capital\n- Creating sustainable creator economies\n\n### Team\n\nSeasoned DeFi innovators with 3+ years of collaborative experience in building successful protocols. Our expertise spans project leadership, technical development, community engagement, and business growth.\n\n### Future\n\nTierra is being built on Berachain, positioning us to become the premier platform for influence verification and community building in the next generation of social finance applications.",
            "# Tierra Mid Memo\n\nPerson: Astroboy \nTags: Product\n\n# TIERRA\n\n## Tokenize Your Influence, Amplify Your Impact\n\n**Where Influence Meets Value**\n\nTierra is revolutionizing how real-world influence is quantified, verified, and monetized in the digital age.\n\n## ~~Team~~\n\nSeasoned DeFi innovators with proven track record:\n\n- Diverse expertise spanning project leadership, technical development, community engagement, and business growth\n- Cohesive unit with 3+ years of collaborative experience in DeFi protocols\n\nNotable achievements:\n\n- 2023: Developed Harmony's 3rd largest DEX, securing $550,000 in funding\n- 2024: Created KAVA EVM's leading DEX, driving over $200M in network value\n\nTeam Members:\n\n| **X** | **Role** | **Linkedin** |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| @astroboydefi | Project Leader | https://www.linkedin.com/in/roberto-quintero-4a155015a/ |\n| @EDonaque | CTO | https://www.linkedin.com/in/eugenio-donaque/ |\n| @OxFrancesco_ | CMO |  |\n| @0xArata | Project Manager | https://www.linkedin.com/in/miguel-√°ngel-acu√±a-reboreda-48a115117/ |\n| @maba078 | Business Developer | https://www.linkedin.com/in/mbarrett078/ |\n| @predragus | Designer | https://www.linkedin.com/in/predragus/ |\n| @uxkosta | Designer |  |\n| @bitdeep_ | Back End Dev | https://www.linkedin.com/in/wendelrpereira/ |\n| @MauriceMiot | Front End Dev |  |\n| @RotCax | Front End Dev |  |\n\n## Opportunities to Innovate\n\n| **Opportunities** | **Innovations** |\n| --- | --- |\n| Fragmented social capital validation in Web3 | First comprehensive platform for quantifying and verifying real-world influence |\n| Lack of verifiable real-world connections | Personal verification system (PoM) bridging digital and physical interactions |\n| Ineffective influence measurement tools | Achievement system with customizable quests and verifiable milestones |\n| Limited creator monetization options | Integrated system combining influence metrics with value creation |\n| Isolated community spaces | Planet NFTs enabling scalable, gamified community building |\n\n## Business Model\n\n| **Influence Verification Network** | **Community Space Ecosystem** | **Revenue Generation** |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Personal verification system for real-world connections (PoM) | Planet NFTs for community building | Multi-tier subscription model |\n| Achievement badges platform with customizable quests | Tiered access through Rocket system | Creator economy monetization |\n| Social capital quantification metrics | Gamified engagement features | Enterprise solutions |\n| Cross-platform influence aggregation | Community-driven growth mechanics | Advertising marketplace |\n\n## Revenue Streams\n\n|  | **Features** | **Monetization Method** | **Target Users** |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| **Premium Features** | Enhanced profile capabilities, Analytics dashboard, Network data access | Subscription-based | Active users, Professionals |\n| **Creator Services** | Planet NFT marketplace, Rocket system, Community tools, Token launch services | Transaction fees, Platform fees | Content creators, Communities |\n| **Marketing Solutions** | Strategic ad placements, Creator promotions | Advertisement fees | Brands, Projects |\n| **Enterprise Services** | Achievement systems, Corporate verification, Event integrations | Custom solutions | Companies, Organizations |\n\n## Market Size\n\n| **Professional Networking Market** | **Web3 Events Ecosystem** | **Creator Economy** |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| LinkedIn: 310M+ monthly active users | 200+ major Web3 events annually | Global market value: $250B+ |\n| Target: Web3 professionals and creators (1-2% initial penetration) | Average attendance: 2,000-5,000 per event | Web3 creator segment: 300,000+ |\n| Estimated serviceable market: 3-6M users | Potential PoM verifications: 400,000+ annually | Community management tools market growth: 40% annually |\n\n## Go-To-Market Strategy\n\n| **Growth Strategy** | **Community Activation** | KOL partnerships and ambassador program | **Target Market** |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|  |  | Strategic ecosystem collaborations | 3.5M bArtio addresses |\n|  |  | Event-driven engagement initiatives | High engagement Web3 users |\n|  | **Feature Rollout** | Phased deployment of core features | Active community participants |\n|  |  | Community-driven feature prioritization |  |\n|  |  | Regular platform enhancements |  |\n|  | **Market Expansion** | Cross-chain compatibility planning |  |\n|  |  | Regional community building |  |\n| **Retention Strategy** | **Engagement** **Mechanics** | Gamified platform interaction |  |\n|  |  | Achievement-based rewards |  |\n|  |  | Community recognition systems |  |\n|  | **Value Creation** | Enhanced networking opportunities |  |\n|  |  | Measurable influence growth |  |\n|  |  | Community development tools |  |\n|  | **Ecosystem Benefits** | Cross-platform integration |  |\n|  |  | Partnership advantages |  |\n|  |  | Exclusive feature access |  |\n\n## Minimum Viable Product (Needs to be updated)\n\n| **Phase** | **Timeline** | **Objectives** | **Key Deliverable** |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Market Validation | October 2024 | Platform concept validation | Community platform foundation |\n| Pre-Alpha Version | November 2024 | Core feature testing | Basic functionality release |\n| Alpha Version | January 2025 | User acquisition | Proof of Meeting |\n\n## Behind Tierra\n\n| **Partner** | **Service** |\n| --- | --- |\n| CAVE | Social coverage |\n| Beraland | Social coverage |\n| Kodiak | DEX liquidity |\n| Beranames | DNS |\n| Kingdomly | NFT |\n| Onikuma | Built-in game |\n\n### ROADMAP\n\n---\n\n[https://brazen-handle-011.notion.site/Tierra-2-0-Internal-Roadmap-1459e00f27868024b4d2fa4f60c9d55e](https://www.notion.so/Tierra-2-0-Internal-Roadmap-1459e00f27868024b4d2fa4f60c9d55e?pvs=21)",
            "# Tierra: The Cosmic Genesis\n\nPerson: Astroboy \nTags: Community\n\n## **Tierra: The Cosmic Genesis**\n\nIn the vast expanse of the digital cosmos, Tierra emerges as a hub for creators and communities seeking to harness the power of influence and connection. The platform offers a universe where digital identities are not only verified but celebrated, and where every interaction holds potential for growth and impact.\n\n## **Generation 0: The Genesis Stars**\n\n**Name:** Tierra: The Genesis Stars\n\n**Short Description:** A limited collection of NFTs representing the founding members of Tierra's cosmic ecosystem. Each Genesis Star grants holders exclusive privileges and marks them as pioneers in the digital influence revolution.\n\n**Mint Details**\n\n- Platform: Kingdomly\n- Chain: Arbitrum\n- Launch Date: 10 January\n- Type: Static Collection (Non generative)\n- Total Supply: 3000 NFTs\n- Mint Price: 0,003 ETH\n- Limit per Wallet: 6 NFTs\n\n**Mint Groups**\n\n1. **Cosmic Pioneers**¬†(Early Testers): Reserved for the first explorers who helped shape Tierra's universe through MVP testing.\n- Supply: 23 NFTs\n- Price: Free Mint\n- Limit per wallet: 1\n- Eligibility: Verified MVP1 testers only\n1. **Cosmic Ambassadors** (Partners): Chosen emissaries from allied communities who help expand Tierra's influence across the digital universe\n- Supply: 500 NFTs\n- Price: Free Mint\n- Limit per wallet: 1\n- Eligibility: Partners can raffle NFTs to their community members\n1. **Cosmic Crew**¬†(Public): Brave souls embarking on the first public expedition into Tierra's digital frontier, forging the foundation of our expanding universe\n- Supply: 2477 NFTs\n- Price: 0.003 ETH\n- Whitelist Price: 0.0024 ETH (-20% for Polar Bear Role holders)\n- Limit per wallet: 5\n- Eligibility:\n    - Public: First come, first served\n    - Whitelist: Must have Polar Bear Role in Discord for discount\n\n**Utility & Benefits**\n\n- Exclusive Discord roles and private channels access\n- Access to App private-beta since now\n- Special \"Genesis Pioneer\" badge in Tierra app\n- Guaranteed Airdrop eligibility\n\n**Tiered Benefits Structure**\n\n**1 NFT Holder**\n\n- Basic Airdrop allocation\n- Genesis Pioneer badge\n\n**2-3 NFT Holder**\n\n- 2x Airdrop allocation multiplier\n- Genesis Pioneer badge with silver trim\n\n**4-5-6 NFT Holder (Maximum)**\n\n- 3x airdrop allocation multiplier\n- Genesis Pioneer badge with gold trim\n- Priority access to future collection mints\n\n## Calendar Event\n\n| **Event** | **Date** |\n| --- | --- |\n| Collection Announcement | December 13th |\n| What can be done? (Blog) | December 20th |\n| Partners Roster | January 3rd |\n| Promotional Video | January 8th |\n\n## **FAQs**\n\n**Q: What makes Genesis Stars special?**\n\nA: Genesis Stars represent the founding members of Tierra's ecosystem, granting exclusive access and benefits that won't be available to later collections.\n\n**Q: How many Genesis Stars can I mint?**\n\nA: Each wallet can mint up to 6 Genesis Stars NFTs.\n\n**Q: Does owning multiple Genesis Stars increase my benefits?**\n\nA: Yes, each additional Genesis Star (up to the maximum of 6 per wallet) increases your airdrop allocation multiplier and unlocks enhanced privileges. Holding more NFTs demonstrates stronger commitment to the ecosystem and is rewarded accordingly.\n\n**Q: Do Cosmic Pioneers & Cosmic Ambassadors get the same benefits as public mint holders?**\n\nA: Yes, Cosmic Pioneers & Cosmic Ambassadors ****who mint their free NFT receive the same tiered benefits as public mint holders. For example, a Cosmic Pioneer with 1 NFT receives the basic airdrop allocation and Genesis Pioneer badge, just like public mint holders.\n\n**Q: Can Cosmic Pioneers & Cosmic Ambassadors participate in the public mint to increase their benefits?**\n\nA: Yes, Cosmic Pioneers & Cosmic Ambassadors can participate in the public mint to acquire additional NFTs (up to the 6 NFT wallet limit) and unlock higher tier benefits. Their free mint counts towards their total NFT count for determining benefit tiers.\n\n**Q: How can I access the whitelist discount for the public mint?**\n\nA: To qualify for the -20% discount, you must meet two requirements:\n\n1. Have the Polar Bear Role in our Discord server\n2. Verify your wallet through our Discord wallet verification system\n\nHaving only the Discord role without completing wallet verification will not grant access to the discount.\n\n**Q: Will Generation 0: Genesis Stars have additional utility in the future?**\n\nA: Yes, Genesis Stars holders will receive priority access to future features and additional benefits as the ecosystem expands.\n\n## Partners Roster\n\n| **Name** | **Confirmed?** |\n| --- | --- |\n| Kingdomly | Yes |\n| Onikuma | Yes |\n| Beranames |  |\n| Cave |  |\n| Kodiak |  |\n| Ramen |  |\n| Infrared | Yes |\n| Beraji | Yes |\n| Yeet | Yes |\n| HoneyJar |  |\n| Azex | Yes |\n| BeraPoker |  |\n| Deek |  |\n| Berabot |  |\n| IVX |  |\n| MemeSwap | Yes |\n| Ooga Booga |  |\n\n## **Roadmap**\n\n**Phase 1: Cosmic Dawn**\n\n(Q1 2024)\n\n- Genesis Stars NFT Collection Launch\n- Exclusive Beta Access for NFT Holders\n- Pioneer Badge System Implementation\n- $TRR Token Launch on bArtio\n\n**Phase 2: Stellar Evolution**\n\n(Q2 2024)\n\n- Planetary Realms NFT Collection Release\n- Proof of Meeting (PoM) Protocol Integration\n- Tierra AI Assistant Launch\n- Strategic Honey Jar Campaign\n\n**Phase 3: Universal Expansion**\n\n(Q3 2024)\n\n- Public Platform Beta Release\n- Planet System Integration\n- Advanced Achievement System\n- Ecosystem Partnership Network\n\n## **Team**\n\n**Core Leadership**\n\n- **Roberto (Astroboy)**¬†- CEO\n    - Self-taught Web3 innovator with 3+ years leading DeFi initiatives\n    - Focus on user-friendly applications and community growth\n- **Francesco**¬†- CMO\n    - Web3 Researcher and Business Developer\n    - DeFi specialist since 2019, community management expert\n\n**Project Management**\n\n- **Miguel**¬†- Project Manager\n    - Experienced software engineer\n    - Background in blockchain and DeFi\n    - Computer Engineering graduate\n\n**Development**\n\n- **Eugenio**¬†- CTO\n    - Full-stack Software Engineer\n    - Expert in Python, Django, DevOps, and blockchain development\n- **Wendel**¬†- Smart Contract & AI Developer\n    - DeFi Protocol Architect\n    - Blockchain Security Expert\n\n**Design**\n\n- **Kosta & Predrag**¬†- Product Designers\n    - Adria Studio founders\n    - Specialists in user-friendly interfaces and product design",
            "# Tierra V2 Walkthrough (Designers)\n\nPerson: 0xArata\nTags: Product\n\nLink to figma with flows (click on prototype in edit mode): https://www.figma.com/design/5wDZ9w2tQezqAuFNHBLG5m/tierra-v2-app-flow?node-id=0-1&t=NuOhF7WBdnJRIxU2-1\n\n## Summary & Context\n\nSince the first MVP/Concept we had in August this year, we have been sculpting and transforming Tierra to offer users a breath of fresh air in the SocialFi world.\nWithout going too far, we have discarded the initial idea of mixing the main concepts of Twitter/Instagram/Tiktok, which was essentially to focus our activity on posting and creating our own multimedia content. We still keep the idea of launching tokens but we have put it on the back burner to accompany it with other elements.\n\nTierra from now on will focus on 6 concepts:\n\n- Tracking of users' on chain activity.\n- User portfolio tracking (DeBank style). **(Already contemplated before)**\n- Creation of private spaces for KOLs and influencers in the purest friendtech style. Called Planets.\n- Launching of memecoins. Called Stars. **(Already contemplated before)**\n- Internal system of influence based on points. Earned through medals and quests.\n- Proof of Meeting, a new way to gain real influence that serves to counteract and balance the fact that a social application is only through a screen. PoM is a system that forces users to meet in real life to exchange their contact information via NFC technology (to be defined).\n\nAs we can see, we will have two types of users:\n\n- The content creator (KOLs, Influencers, Companies).\n- The consumer of that content.\n\nThe essential difference lies in the fact that the former will be the owners of these private spaces (Planets). These private spaces will have the capacity to:\n\n- Host a forum, where the content creator will be able to publish on the topics he/she considers (although we initially want to focus on financial topics). One way to visualise this is to take the example of reddit, where each sub-forum is a planet.\n- Publish events, both face-to-face and digital. Taking the example of Luma to promote the use of PoM among creators and users.\n- Private investments or other information that we/users consider useful in the future. Copy / Paste trading.\n\nAnother important point in the application is the ranking of influence. Users will be able to earn points through the PoM they have in addition to the internal/external quests that we will make available in our application to obtain badges. This will help users to really know who has a real reputation.\n\nHaving set a bit of context, let's move on to what we think are the most important screens and explain a bit about what's on each of them.\n\n---\n\n## App Walkthrough & Wireframes\n\n### Home\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-07 at 18.33.20.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-07_at_18.33.20.png)\n\nThe home screen will mainly collect users' on-chain ‚Äúactivities‚Äù. Similar to twitter, we will have two tabs: One led by the algorithm we implement (For you) and the other by the people the user follows (Following).\n\nThe activities comprise:\n\n- Transactions\n- Proof of meeting actions\n- Achievement of badges\n- Various investments\n- (TBD) Price action & Events\n\nThese activities will have the ability to be commented on (as we had previously with posts), liked, saved and shared.\nIn short, we simply replace posts with activities. We are going to recycle the old screens regarding ‚Äúthread‚Äù and ‚Äúcommenting‚Äù.\n\nIn addition to the main content, at the top we can see 2 buttons and a carousel.\n\n- The buttons are simply, one to go to a screen where the user can manage their referrals, and the other to access their notifications.\n- The carousel will be a space where KOLs will be able to promote their planets.\n\n### Discover\n\nPlanets = Friend Tech Keys\n\nStars = Memecoins \n\nRockets = Users with access to Planets\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-07 at 19.26.21.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-07_at_19.26.21.png)\n\nOn the discover screen the user can explore Planets, Stars and the most influential users on the platform. There will also be a global search engine located in the top right corner.\n\nThe screen that derives from clicking on Stars, will be the one that we already have as explora in version 1, that is to say, where the tokens were categorised and where the user can click and see the details of any of those.\n\nFrom Planets will be derive another screen with a leaderboard of those planets and another search functionality, ie. another search bar. (This screen needs TBD in wireframe)\n\nLast but not least, we have the section with the profiles highlighted by the influence ranking. This is where PoM and the PoM Card concept comes into play. This will be an infinite scroll.\n\nThe PoM cards are an attractive element for the users where they will show their updated position in the ranking, their avatar, their username and the medals they are most proud of (the number is yet to be defined). These cards will be customizable (as if they were skins) by the users themselves, but they will always have the same skeleton that we have mentioned. Here we need you to put your efforts to get something very appealing to the user.\n\nAny user can follow those just by clicking the top right button inside any card.\n\nWe don‚Äôt know at the time of the creation of this document if we will add another screen if the user taps on one of these cards.\n\n### Control Panel\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-08 at 15.38.36.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-08_at_15.38.36.png)\n\nThis screen is where the user will be able to perform most of the actions in the application in terms of managing their experience on the ground.\nOn the one hand, you will have access to your PoM card in the ‚Äòbanner‚Äô above, where you can see your position, points and medals you have achieved so far.\nBelow this, we can see 4 main sections:\n\n- Your Planets (where the user will be able to access the planets he has bought access to, and if he is a content creator, his own).\n- Your Stars: where the user will be able to access the tokens he follows and those he has launched (any user can deploy tokens).\n- Subscription: here the user can manage subscriptions to our platform. From here you will access a screen similar to the one in X (twitter) where all the features of each of the subscription levels are specified.\n- NFT (TBD): It is possible that we will dedicate a section to the NFTs, however it is an idea that we have not yet defined.\n\n### PoM Card\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-08 at 15.55.17.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-08_at_15.55.17.png)\n\nThis is the screen you access directly when you click on the card at the top from the control panel.\nHere a QR will be displayed (although it is likely that this will change to NFC technology) which users will be able to use to perform the PoM. This will be accompanied by their avatar at the top and, at the bottom, their username + the medals that the user wants to highlight.\n\nAll this information can be modified from an editing menu which can be accessed through the icon in the top right corner.\nThe idea is that users can have custom PoM cards, that is, they can change the background, the colour of the QR, the ‚Äòcase‚Äô of the medals (which I haven't added in the wireframe, but it would be nice to have something like that), what badges he/she wants to show and so on.\nThis opens up an opportunity for us for both revenue and user growth within the application.\n\n### Planet View\n\n![Cell to Singularity: Evolution SS](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/IMG_D7F4FACF366B-1.jpeg)\n\nCell to Singularity: Evolution SS\n\n![Our wireframe](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-08_at_16.15.47.png)\n\nOur wireframe\n\nThis is the main access screen to any planet, take the concept of this screen in a more gamified style. The user when entering here will see in the centre the planet in an idle state, surrounded by satellites (where users can access the different spaces that the Content Creator has to offer value, i.e. the forum, private events, investments, etc.). In other words, each satellite is a feature. The other type of element that will appear are animated rockets/ships that represent users who belong to this community.\nAll these elements will be animated. In addition, the user will be able to swipe inside the planet so that the community can get new and/or better features (TBD). We call this Slide to Earn.\nAs a reference to what we are proposing, I attach an image of a Tap Game called ‚ÄòCell to Singularity: Evolution‚Äô.\n\n### Wallet (V1 and V2)\n\n![Wallet V1](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-08_at_16.39.14.png)\n\nWallet V1\n\n![Wallet V2](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-08_at_16.39.28.png)\n\nWallet V2\n\nHere we maintain the concept we had in August. We will simply extend the financial information to more than just tokens and points. The idea is to add 4 sections: Tokens, LPs, Locked and Investments.\n\n- **LPs**: Liquidity Pools or pairs where the user is invested.\n- **Locked**: Tokens that are invested in a Vesting Contract.\n- **Investments**: other types of investments (like a others section).\n\nThe existence of several versions is due to two stages of the App. *Pre-launch and Public Launch*.\nDuring the pre-launch (V1) we will have the old leaderboard that we have already designed. However, in the second version we will modify the **leaderboard for the PoM one** and we will add a new section/product which will be the **Tierra Vaults** (unique investment opportunities for our users).\n\nThe button in the upper right corner would allow the user to disconnect/change wallet.\n\nAnother highlight is to add a button (which I have represented with emojis üêª‚õìÔ∏è) that will serve the user to add his BeraName on the platform (it is an ENS service in Berachain) and/or buy it through a pop up. \nAs a reference, I attach an image of the DeBank application so that you can understand where we got our inspiration from when we talk about the Tokens/Lp/Locked/Investments section.\n\n![IMG_00C3AE31EC96-1.jpeg](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/IMG_00C3AE31EC96-1.jpeg)\n\n![IMG_496BDB224A3D-1.jpeg](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/IMG_496BDB224A3D-1.jpeg)\n\n### Profile\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-08 at 17.31.51.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-08_at_17.31.51.png)\n\nThe profile screen will retain much of its design.\nWhat we are going to replace the tabs section we had before with another one that will contain the following cards:\n\n- PoM: where you will be able to consult with which people you have carried out the Proof of meeting action.\n- Activity: Similar to what we had before. Only now, depending on the user's subscription, we will show part of the information or all of it.\n- Badges: What medals the user has (the screen is attached in the next section).\n- Astronaut: where users will be able to see which planets (communities) you follow/have created and which stars (tokens) you follow/have created.\n\nIn addition, we will add both the settings and a display of activities that the user has liked/saved.\n\n### Badges\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-08 at 17.37.10.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-08_at_17.37.10.png)\n\nThis is the screen that can be accessed from the profile by clicking on the ‚ÄúBagdes‚Äù card.\nThere are 3 elements to highlight:\n\n- The edit menu. Where the user will be able to decide which medals to show in his medal rack.\n- The medal rack. A limited number of medals (3 for a user without subscription, 6 for one with subscription). This is the same as the one shown on the PoM Card.\n- The complete list of medals. Where an avatar will be shown indicating if the medal is obtained through our project or through others, the name of the medal (where it says Project Name), a brief description of how it is obtained and the design of the medal.\n\nThis document will be updated along the next days.\n\n---\n\n## From Home:\n\n### Notifications\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-14 at 17.28.06.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-14_at_17.28.06.png)\n\nHere we are going to show all the notifications related to the user and the people/planets he/she is following.\n\nI‚Äôve followed more or less the same style as Instagram, where the notifications are grouped by date.\n\nAs you can see, except for the comments in activities, all the notifications styles are the same. Based only on an avatar of the user/planet and then a sentence about the notification itself.\n\n### Referral\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-14 at 17.33.16.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-14_at_17.33.16.png)\n\nVery simplistic screen. I‚Äôve taken the Airbnb example, where the first section explains how the referral works and the second how is your journey in this topic. Ie, the earnings you‚Äôve accumulated until the current date and the list of successful sign ups through your referral link.\n\nAlso, in the bottom of the screen, we have the ctas, in form of copy and the typical button that opens the share system module of the mobile.\n\n## From Discover\n\n### Planet Leaderboard\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-14 at 17.41.48.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-14_at_17.41.48.png)\n\nAfter the user clicks on ‚ÄúPlanets‚Äù from the ‚Äú[Discover](https://www.notion.so/Tierra-V2-Walkthrough-Designers-1379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e?pvs=21)‚Äù screen, it will appear a screen with and ordered list (by popularity) of these private spaces that the user can join in our platform. \n\nFor every card, we will have the avatar of the planet, the name, the owner (username), position and number of current users inside this community.\n\nThe screen will have a search feature to let the user look for a specific planet.\n\nAfter clicking on any of these cards, the user will be redirected to the [Planet View](https://www.notion.so/Tierra-V2-Walkthrough-Designers-1379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e?pvs=21) discussed above.\n\n## From Planet View\n\n### Forum\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 17.09.24.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_17.09.24.png)\n\nAfter clicking on one of the satellites in the planet view, the user will be able to enter its forum. In the purest reddit style, it will be composed of topics where the KOL will post and its followers will be able to comment. This screen will also have a search engine and a sharing button.\n\nAfter clicking on one of the topics we will reuse the thread screen of the first version.\n\n### Events\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 17.47.22.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_17.47.22.png)\n\nAs is done to access the forum, by clicking on one of the planet view satellites, the user will be able to access the events screen. Here is where the KOL can publish both private and public (TBD) events for his followers, as you can see, these can be face-to-face or digital through the platform of his choice.\nIn the absence of defining a detailed event screen, this module is based on the event app called [Luma](https://lu.ma/). (You can download it from App Store to check it out)\n\n![IMG_3BA5D62B2CD4-1.jpeg](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/IMG_3BA5D62B2CD4-1.jpeg)\n\n![IMG_C0D2DBCE232D-1.jpeg](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/IMG_C0D2DBCE232D-1.jpeg)\n\n![IMG_D6FFA7E886A5-1.jpeg](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/IMG_D6FFA7E886A5-1.jpeg)\n\n## From Control Panel\n\n### Your Planets/Your Stars\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 17.55.07.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_17.55.07.png)\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 17.55.22.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_17.55.22.png)\n\nThese two screens share the same skeleton, that is to say, both will have a search engine, both will have two sections where it is specified if the user has any of these two elements and the ones that follow.\nOn the planets side, we will reuse the cards from the leaderboard screen, and on the stars side, we will try to reuse the ones from the explora scrren that was made in the first version of Tierra.\n\n## Subscription\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 17.58.45.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_17.58.45.png)\n\n![IMG_17B30CED237E-1.jpeg](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/IMG_17B30CED237E-1.jpeg)\n\nFor the design of this screen, we have based it on the one that **X/Twitter** has for the purchase of subscriptions, where the user can browse through horizontal slides. The idea is that we group in some way the features that the user will be able to access after the purchase of one of the subscriptions.\nEach feature could have an information button that will open a modal at the bottom of the screen providing detailed information, as well as an icon indicating whether it is available or not with the chosen subscription model.\n\n## From Wallet\n\n### Mint a Beraname\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.06.20.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.06.20.png)\n\nAfter clicking on the button where the bear and the chain are located, the user will access a modal where he/she can buy a beraname and use it in the app. The modal is taken from their own website. https://www.beranames.com/\n\n### PoM Leaderboard\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.08.59.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.08.59.png)\n\nAfter the public release of the app, our idea is to activate PoM in all its glory, including the influence system, or in other words, this screen. In it we will try to show an alternative version of the PoM cards (in horizontal), where we will include the same fields, position, avatar, username, medals and a follow button. Our idea is that this will be appealing, so the first 3 positions will have a different style than the rest of the list. Even more with the one that occupies the first position, since we will assign a greater space to it.\n\n## From Profile\n\n### Following/Followers\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.14.47.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.14.47.png)\n\nTypical screen where the user can consult the followers/followed/followed/followed in common that another user has in the form of a list. Each item in the list contains, avatar, username, biography and a button to follow.\n\n### PoM in Common\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.16.46.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.16.46.png)\n\nThis screen will show the PoMs that the user has in common with the user you are querying to know with whom he/she has a real contact. The design of the cards should be quite similar to the PoM leaderboard, where we show, avatar, username, medals and position in the leaderboard.\n\n### Astronaut\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.19.17.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.19.17.png)\n\nAs we did with Your Planets/Your Stars, the screen that derived from the control panel, we will show the same information to the public on a single screen with two tabs.\n\n### PoM\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.21.10.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.21.10.png)\n\nIf you remember the higlighted profiles section of the discover screen, we used to show the PoM cards of the top users of the platform. The idea is to recycle those cards and put them in this screen, where the user will be able to access the PoM of the user he is consulting.\n\n### Activities\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.23.39.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.23.39.png)\n\nThis screen will show the activities of the user that is being consulted, we will recycle the same elements of the home screen. Our idea is also that those users who do not have a subscription will only be able to see the 10 oldest activities and the rest will be blurred.\n\n### Saved\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.26.16.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.26.16.png)\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.28.41.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.28.41.png)\n\nThis screen will house all those items that the user has both saved and liked. By default, we will provide the user with 3 lists differentiated by type of element, i.e. Activities, Planets and Stars. However, the user will be able to create his own lists where any type of element can be stored as shown in the second screen (Custom List).\n\n### Settings\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-22 at 18.29.23.png](Tierra%20V2%20Walkthrough%20(Designers)%201379e00f278680f18f4ade1ae5b2293e/Screenshot_2024-11-22_at_18.29.23.png)\n\nAlthough we have not defined all the settings that the app will need, keep in mind that we will be using this screen throughout the development of the product, so we would appreciate having some skeleton to rely on.",
            "Luganodes | Exploring Berachain and Proof of Liquidity\n\n# Exploring Berachain and Proof of Liquidity\n\nPoL: Stirring the Crypto Waters\n\nPublished on\n\n28 Mar, 2024\n\nCopy Link[](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Check%20out%20this%20blog%20by%20Luganodes%20-%20%22Exploring%20Berachain%20and%20Proof%20of%20Liquidity%22&url=)[](https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=&title=Exploring%20Berachain%20and%20Proof%20of%20Liquidity&summary=Check%20out%20this%20blog%20by%20Luganodes%20-%20%22Exploring%20Berachain%20and%20Proof%20of%20Liquidity%22)\n\n## Introduction\n\nBerachain is an Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) compatible Layer-1 blockchain that uses a novel consensus mechanism called \"Proof of Liquidity.\" In 2023, it raised $42 million in a private funding round led by Polychain Capital. In March of this year, Bloomberg reported that Berachain raised $69 million in its latest funding round led by Brevan Howard Digital and Framework Ventures. Upon completing this funding round, it expects to reach a $1.5 billion valuation.\n\nThis article will explore the Berachain ecosystem, including its three tokens and Proof of Liquidity consensus mechanism. First, we'll examine the Berachain EVM.\n\n## EVM Equivalent vs EVM Compatible\n\nThe Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) is Ethereum's runtime environment for executing smart contracts. It provides an isolated, secure space for running smart contracts on its blockchain. Furthermore, the EVM has a set of supported operations (opcodes), smart contract languages (like Solidity and Vyper), and tooling (Hardhat, Remix, and Foundry).\n\nSo, an EVM-equivalent blockchain seeks to replicate the entire environment and functionality of the EVM and support the same operations, smart contract languages, and tools. The goal is to create a seamless experience for users and developers transitioning from Ethereum to the new chain.\n\n## EVM Compatible\n\nAn EVM-compatible blockchain supports a degree of interoperability with Ethereum without replicating the entire environment. It could support smart contract languages and tools to a certain extent while maintaining differences in security, functionality, or performance.\n\n## Berachain EVM\n\nAs mentioned, Berachain is an EVM-compatible Layer-1 blockchain. Thus, it supports the same operations and tooling as the EVM while bringing additional functionality that optimizes for its Proof of Liquidity consensus mechanism. Therefore, the team considers Berachain an \"EVM-equivalent-plus\" blockchain.\n\n## Polaris EVM\n\nBerachain's technology is built on Polaris, a high-performance blockchain framework for building chains on top of the CometBFT consensus engine. The Polaris EVM provides the execution environment for Berachain smart contracts and is where Berachain's EVM compatibility emanates. Berachain developed the Polaris EVM to build a modular stack to separate the EVM runtime layer and provide an improved EVM experience.\n\n## CometBFT Consensus\n\nThe concept of Byzantine Fault Tolerance (BFT) has been around for decades but recently gained popularity due to the success of blockchain technology. Blockchain technology is a modernization of BFT. It provides a way for chains to handle machine failures even if the machine becomes malicious.\n\nCometBFT is a BFT middleware that securely replicates a state transition machine on many machines. It is a fork of Tendermint Core, and security is guaranteed so long as less than one-third of the machines on the network fail in any way. CometBFT consists of two primary components:\n\n1.  Its user-friendly and highly performant application interface.\n\n2.  The consensus engine is based on the Tendermint consensus algorithm. Tendermint ensures that all the machines record the same transactions and that they're in the correct order.\n\n## BERA, BGT, and HONEY\n\nBerachain has a tri-token system with BERA, BGT, and HONEY. BERA is sometimes called the \"gas token\" because it sends transactions on the blockchain. In other words, it pays for the transaction's gas. BERA tokens are available through various Berachain Testnet Faucets.\n\nBGT stands for \"Bera Governance Token.\" In PoS networks, blockchains use a governance token to secure the network through staking. Likewise, Berachain uses BGT for delegating in its Proof of Liquidity model. To acquire BGT, a user must first deposit liquidity in the BEX. On the BEX, users can swap tokens, provide liquidity to the BEX, and earn BGT rewards.\n\nBerachain uses HONEY to stabilize the protocol. It's a stablecoin that pegs approximately 1-to-1 with USDC. Users must first get BERA from a Berachain Testnet Faucet, then swap BERA for HONEY on Berachain's Native BEX.\n\n## Berachain Liquidity Pools\n\nBerachain offers flexible pool types to support various swap paradigms, weighted pools, and more. All of the pools adhere to a standard pool interface for user interaction.\n\nCreating pools is permissionless; thus, anyone can create a new pool on the BEX. First, the pool creator must determine the type of pool they want. Next, creators in the BEX must provide the liquidity to start the initial pool.\n\nCurrent pool types in the BEX include the Balanced Pool Type, which features a weighted asset pool. To create a Balanced Pool Type, the creator must configure and provide for the following:\n\n1.  The token set.\n\n2.  Between 2 to 8 tokens in the pool.\n\n3.  Initial liquidity.\n\n4.  Token weights in the pool.\n\n5.  The fee paid to Liquidity Providers during swaps.\n\nHere is an example: We have $100 worth of HONEY and want to pair it against BERA separately. In a traditional pool, the breakdown would look like this:\n\n$50 of `$HONEY` paired with $50 of `$BERA`\n\n$50 of `$HONEY` paired with $50 of $stgUSDC\n\nInitially, Berachain will launch a set of House Pools. The goal is to have these pools flush with deep liquidity so they can create MetaPools. A MetaPool contains at least one Liquidity Provider token. A Liquidity Provider token represents shares in a liquidity pool.\n\n## Proof of Stake Downsides\n\nNext, we'll look at Berachain's consensus mechanism. But to better understand Berachain's Proof of Liquidity consensus mechanism, let's first examine some of the disadvantages of Proof of Stake (PoS), a widespread consensus mechanism used in blockchain technology. In PoS consensus, token holders can validate transactions and create new blocks based on their stake, which the protocol holds as collateral.\n\nOne of the disadvantages of PoS is that improved security can lead to a reduction in liquidity. Participants stake tokens to become validators and delegators who receive rewards and secure the network. However, the stake can become centralized if newly minted tokens continuously go to the same participants. Below is a more complete list of the disadvantages:\n\n1.  Liquidity Issues: Securing the chain can lead to a reduction in liquidity.\n\n2.  Stake Centralization: The stake can become centralized.\n\n3.  Insufficient Validator Incentives: Validators can receive minimal rewards for their work securing the network.\n\nThus, Proof of Liquidity is a novel consensus mechanism developed to address some of the PoS model's shortcomings. It seeks to overcome the challenges faced by networks striving to remain decentralized and align network incentives between validators and the project ecosystem.\n\n## Proof of Liquidity Consensus Mechanism\n\nWith Proof of Liquidity, the goal is to increase security by increasing liquidity.\n\nBerachain's Proof of Liquidity addresses the above four issues with PoS through these various mechanisms:\n\n1.  Liquidity Issues: BGT (the delegation token) is separated from BERA (the gas token). Hence, the staking token differs from the one used for other on-chain actions. Users can only earn new BGT by providing liquidity to the BEX, which incentivizes further liquidity.\n\n2.  Stake Centralization: To address PoS centralization issues, Berachain distributes new BGT to liquidity providers. Because stake is distributed to separate market participants rather than directly to stakers, token inflation is more fairly and evenly distributed than in traditional PoS chains.\n\n3.  Insufficient Validator Incentives: Proof of Liquidity addresses the third issue with PoS by incentivizing protocols and validators to work together. Berachain aligns its goals by having validators incentivize a protocol's Liquidity Provider pool via BGT. Additionally, protocols help those validators accumulate more BGT stakes via bribes (see below).\n\nBerachain's Proof Of Liquidity model focuses on three objectives:\n\n1.  Build liquidity.\n\n2.  Solve the stake centralization challenge.\n\n3.  Align validator incentives with protocols.\n\nWith Proof of Liquidity, participants contribute liquidity to pools and receive governance tokens as a reward. These tokens are vital to the delegation process within the Proof of Liquidity system. In the case of Berachain, the governance token is BGT. Users add liquidity to BEX liquidity pools to earn BGT in return. They can then delegate their BGT tokens to validators.\n\nAs mentioned, a primary distinction of a Proof of Liquidity consensus is that the network's delegation and gas tokens differ. Berachain seeks to bolster liquidity, improve capital efficiency, and synchronize the project's ecosystem goals with the validators by decoupling these tokens.\n\nContributing liquidity to the BEX is the exclusive way to obtain new BGT tokens. This requirement motivates users to participate in liquidity pools and makes Proof of Liquidity a more active version of PoS, where delegators lend their tokens to a validator. With Berachain, the protocols receive all of the participants' liquidity. By bootstrapping liquidity, Berachain can accomplish more with fewer resources. That could be an essential distinction given all the new Layer 1s rolling out.\n\nSo, we've learned that Proof of Liquidity is an innovative consensus mechanism that addresses some of the issues found in PoS. Next, we'll explore Berachain's validators and their vital role in the network's security and consensus mechanism.\n\n## Validators and Delegators\n\nTo participate in Proof of Liquidity, users must acquire BGT tokens by providing liquidity to the BEX.\n\nIn Proof of Liquidity, validators earn BGT rewards when they propose a new block. These rewards include transaction fees and block rewards, which pay for their role. The network randomly selects validators to propose new blocks or attest to the validity of proposed blocks.\n\nRandom selection is weighted by the amount of BGT a validator has. Thus, validators produce blocks proportionally based on the amount of BGT delegated to them. The greater the delegation weight, the higher the validator's chance of block production.\n\nLuganodes is a AAA rated institutional-grade staking service provider for individuals and enterprises. Now you can take part in validating blockchain transactions and earn rewards. Learn about crypto staking with Luganodes here.\n\nA validator's stake weight determines two things:\n\n1.  How many blocks a validator produces in comparison to the other validators?\n\n2.  What percentage of future BGT emissions can their votes set?\n\nThe validator determines which Liquidity Provider pools are incentivized for users to deposit their tokens. The amount of BGT delegated to a validator determines the BGT inflation the validator controls. BGT inflation directed towards the native BEX liquidity pools means deeper liquidity for those pools.\n\nLet's assume a validator has 5% of all the staked BGT delegated to them. That validator controls 5% of where future BGT inflation will be directed.\n\nThose who don't want to be a validator can acquire BGT and delegate their tokens to network validators to earn more BGT by providing liquidity to the BEX liquidity pools. Those who don't want to delegate their BGT tokens to earn rewards can burn them for BERA.\n\nBGT tokens delegated to a validator can be used to create and vote on governance proposals. After a validator receives BGT rewards, they are responsible for sharing a percentage of the awards with specific liquidity pools through a precompiled contract called \"Berachef.\" BGT incentivizes validators to behave honestly. Validators also get to vote on future BGT inflation across multiple liquidity pools.\n\nThe amount of BGT rewards earned by a user for staking liquidity per pool is based on a few factors like the BGT amount emitted to that pool and the amount of liquidity that the user provided to that pool (out of all liquidity in the pool)\n\nThe main takeaway is that delegators and validators receive rewards, creating a symbiotic ecosystem where all parties benefit.\n\n## Berachain‚Äôs Cutting Boards\n\nBreaking down which Liquidity Provider pools will receive future BGT inflation is called creating a \"Cutting Board.\"\n\nValidators can choose to split up their Berachef weights in different ways. One Liquidity Provider pool could receive 100% of the BGT inflation emissions, or multiple Liquidity Provider pools could receive percentages of the validator's BGT inflation emissions, which total 100%.\n\nFor example, 75% of the BGT inflation could go to BERA/HONEY and 25% to the USDT/HONEY pool.\n\n## Bribe Mechanics on Berachain\n\nIn most contexts, \"bribe\" is an unsavory term and can even describe an illegal action. However, with Berachain's Proof of Liquidity model, Bribes are a way for validators to incentivize network participants to delegate BGT tokens to them instead of others.\n\nValidators offer Bribes to their BGT delegators, and it's a way for validators to differentiate themselves from the crowd of other validators above and beyond the standard metrics for gauging validator performance.\n\nFor validators that have created Bribes, they are distributed to their delegators as follows:\n\n-   A Bribe is handed out each time a validator chosen for the Bribe proposes a new block.\n\n-   Bribes can be set for a future epoch but must be set before the epoch begins.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe testnet is live now, and Berachain's mainnet is set to launch in the second quarter of 2024. With its innovative Proof of Liquidity model, Berachain is poised to better align the incentives across its ecosystem and could play an influencer role in how Web3 platforms use liquidity.\n"
